//fldigi macro definition file extended
// This file defines the macro structure(s) for the digital modem program, fldigi
// It also serves as a basis for any macros that are written by the user
//
// The top line of this file should always be the first line in every macro 
// definition file (.mdf) for the fldigi program to recognize it as such.
//

//
// Macro # 1
/$ 0 HD1 MT63-500S @>|
<MODEM:MT63-500S><GOFREQ:1500><TX>\n
HAM_DIGITAL_1: Charm at the Sheraton since 2018\n
HAM_DIGITAL_1: Charm at the Sheraton since 2018\n
HAM_DIGITAL_1: Charm at the Sheraton since 2018\n
<RX>

//
// Macro # 2
/$ 1 HD2 RTTY-75W @>|
<MODEM:RTTY:850:75:5><GOFREQ:1000><TX>\n
HAM_DIGITAL_2: 2020 TO 2021 WERE THE OFF YEARS\n
HAM_DIGITAL_2: 2020 TO 2021 WERE THE OFF YEARS\n
HAM_DIGITAL_2: 2020 TO 2021 WERE THE OFF YEARS\n
<RX>

//
// Macro # 3
/$ 2 HD3 OLIVIA-16/1K @>|
<MODEM:OLIVIA-16/1K><GOFREQ:2000><TX>\n
HAM_DIGITAL_3: Red vs Blue: Modern Active Directory Attacks & Defense by Sean Metcalf\n
HAM_DIGITAL_3: Red vs Blue: Modern Active Directory Attacks & Defense by Sean Metcalf\n
HAM_DIGITAL_3: Red vs Blue: Modern Active Directory Attacks & Defense by Sean Metcalf\n
<RX>

//
// Macro # 4
/$ 3 HD4 BPSK250 @>|
<MODEM:BPSK250><GOFREQ:1200><TX>\n
HAM_DIGITAL_4: Exploiting Buffers Overflows 101 by Kyle Hanslovan & John Ferrell\n
HAM_DIGITAL_4: Exploiting Buffers Overflows 101 by Kyle Hanslovan & John Ferrell\n
HAM_DIGITAL_4: Exploiting Buffers Overflows 101 by Kyle Hanslovan & John Ferrell\n
<RX>

//
// Macro # 5
/$ 4 HD5 THOR16  @>|
<MODEM:THOR16><GOFREQ:750><TX>\n
HAM_DIGITAL_5: Rob M Lee Keynoting in 2017 and 2026\n
HAM_DIGITAL_5: Rob M Lee Keynoting in 2017 and 2026\n
HAM_DIGITAL_5: Rob M Lee Keynoting in 2017 and 2026\n
<RX>

//
// Macro # 6
/$ 5 HD6 FSKHELL105 @>|
<MODEM:FSKH105><GOFREQ:1400><TX>\n
HAM_DIGITAL_6: DELOREAN DMC THEMED 2025\n
HAM_DIGITAL_6: DELOREAN DMC THEMED 2025\n
HAM_DIGITAL_6: DELOREAN DMC THEMED 2025\n
<RX>

